cs.IT, cs.IS, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.DS. 

This paper deals with information theory and communication systems, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The paper also involves the study of mutual information and entropy, which are relevant to cs.IS (Information Theory). The use of side information and decoding techniques can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia), while the investigation of the rate region for various settings falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper also involves the study of lossless source coding, which can be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
